# Git & Branching

## Branch naming
- `main` — production-ready, protected. No direct pushes.
- `develop` — integration branch. PRs merge here first.
- `feature/<ticket-or-name>` — new features
- `fix/<description>` — bug fixes
- `chore/<description>` — maintenance, deps, CI
- `refactor/<description>` — structural changes, no behavior change

## Commits
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `perf:`, `ci:`
- Atomic commits — one logical change per commit.
- Imperative mood: "add event buffer" not "added event buffer".
- First line under 72 chars. Body for non-obvious changes.

## Pull requests
- Small and focused. One feature/fix per PR. 10+ files = consider splitting.
- Every PR: clear title, description of what/why, test plan.
- Require at least one review. Squash merge. Delete branch after merge.

## Protected branches
- `main` and `develop` protected. No force pushes, no direct commits. All changes through PRs with passing CI.
